{"title": "Whole Foods is getting in-store Black Friday discounts on Amazon Echo, Echo Plus, and Fire TV", "content": " \nSince Amazon bought Whole Foods in August, it\u2019s doing things a little differently this Black Friday. The two are teaming up to offer in-store discounts on Amazon devices, including the Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Fire TV, and Fire tablets, at over 100 Whole Foods stores.\nAmazon\u2019s also going to be adding pop-up stores, staffed with Amazon employees, to select Whole Foods locations in Illinois, Michigan, Florida, California, and Colorado, starting on November 13th. It\u2019s not yet known if these deals will also be available online.\nBeginning the week before Black Friday, Amazon will offer the following deals in Whole Food stores:\n\n\nEcho Dot for $29.99 (usually $49.99)\n\nAmazon Echo for $79.99 (usually $99.99)\n\nEcho Plus for $119.99  (usually $149.99)\n\nKindle Paperwhite for $89.99 (usually $119.99)\n\nAmazon Cloud Cam for $99.99 (usually $119.99)\n\nFire 7 Tablet for $29.99 (usually $49.99)\n\nFire HD 8 Tablet for $49.99 (usually $79.99)\n\nAmazon has its own online Black Friday plans but it hasn\u2019t announced specific deals yet.\nVox Media has affiliate partnerships. These do not influence editorial content, though Vox Media may earn commissions for products purchased via affiliate links. For more information, see our ethics policy.\n\n\n"}
